THis file contains instructions for managing code (git, documentation, ...)


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Code Documentation
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
run the following repeatedly until no errors exist ot get the code documentation clean

devtools::document()

To create package documentation

On Linux (sc)
1. cd to the project directory
2. run roxygen2::roxygenize(). This will create the Rd files in the man directory of the main package directory
3. on Linux, cd to the diretory above the package directory
4. run R CMD Rd2pdf <packagename>

On Windows ....
Pointing to pdflatex ...

Sys.setenv(PATH=paste(Sys.getenv("PATH"),"C:/Program Files/MiKTeX 2.9/miktex/bin/x64/",sep=";"))

Running documentation - this builds the file toxvaldb09_manual.pdf


Sys.setenv(PATH = paste(Sys.getenv("PATH"), "C:/Program Files/MiKTeX 2.9/miktex/bin/x64", sep=.Platform$path.sep))
Sys.setenv(R_PAPERSIZE="letter")
system("R CMD Rd2pdf . --title=toxvaldb09 toxvaldb09 --output=../toxvaldb92_manual.pdf --force --no-clean --internals")

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Managing git and bitbucket - internal
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To get a GitHub token
1. Log into GitHub https://github.com
2. At the top right, click on your profile picture to open your profile pane and select "Settings"
3. At the bottom of the left panel, select "Developer settings"
4. At left, select "Personal access tokens"
5. Select "Tokens (classic)"
6. At the top, select "Generate new token", then "Generate new token (classic)"
7. Give the token an informative name in the "Note" field
8. Set expiration to 90 days (security requirment for tokens to expire, just like passwords)
9. Select the "repo" checkbox
10. Scroll to the bottom of the form and clicl "Generate token"
11. Save this token string for future reference
12. Click the "Confirugre SSO" dropdown menu on the token and click "USEPA" to allow SSO authorization

To clone the ToxVal_Stage repo
1. Make a folder on the Linux drive
2. Open an RStudio session and a terminal (or use a local terminal with git installed)
  a. Select the git tab at the top right. Under the "More" dropdown menu, select "new terminal"
3. Set working directory to the new folder
4. Clone the ToxVal_Stage repo (can be HTTPS, SSH, etc. depending on environment setup needs)
  `> git clone https://github.com/USEPA/ToxVal_Stage.git`
5. You will be prompted for your username and password. This is your github username and the access token you just created
6. If all is well, this will pull the package down into a subfolder of the one you created above.
7. Contact the team lead if any issues occur.

Additional useful commands:

git config --global user.name "*User name*"
git config --global user.email "*Email*"

git config --get remote.origin.url
git remote add origin https://github.com/USEPA/ToxVal_Stage.git

git push -u origin master

